cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.DC, cs.HC 

This paper discusses the security implications of ad blocking and proposes new techniques to evade detection. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the practicality and legality of these techniques, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.CY (Computers and Society). The paper also mentions the growth of the web, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of these techniques on user experience, which could fall under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
